{"timestamp": "2025-12-05 04:24:02.881169", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\n\nExecutive summary\n- Overall OSPF control-plane and core/server connectivity are healthy.\n- A targeted outage affects hosts in subnet 10.2.1.0/24: they receive an incorrect default gateway via DHCP, breaking reachability to DNS and the server farm.\n- Fault localized to DHCP configuration for 10.2.1.0/24 on dhcp_server.\n\nObserved symptoms\n- host_1_1_1_1 (10.1.1.24) can resolve and access web0.local and web99.local with normal timings. Pings to DNS (10.200.0.2), load balancer (10.200.0.7), and web servers succeed.\n- host_2_1_1_1 (10.2.1.12) fails curl tests to web0.local and web99.local (0.0s timings and multi-second totals indicating lookup/connect failure). Pings to DNS, load balancer, web servers, core/router addresses all fail with “Destination Host Unreachable” from 10.2.1.12.\n\nOSPF and routing health\n- OSPF adjacencies are Full across the core, distribution, and server_access_router:\n  - router_core_1, router_core_2, router_core_3: all neighbors Full.\n  - router_dist_1_1, router_dist_2_1: neighbors Full with cores.\n  - server_access_router: Full neighbor to core_3.\n- Routing tables are consistent:\n  - server_access_router has 10.200.0.0/24 connected and OSPF routes to all access subnets.\n  - router_dist_1_1 has 10.1.1.0/24 connected and OSPF to server farm and other subnets.\n  - router_dist_2_1 has 10.2.1.0/24 connected on br0 (IP 10.2.1.1) and OSPF to server farm and other subnets.\n\nPer-host IP/DNS configuration\n- host_1_1_1_1: 10.1.1.24/24, default via 10.1.1.1, nameserver 10.200.0.2.\n- host_2_1_1_1: 10.2.1.12/24, default via 10.2.1.254, nameserver 10.200.0.2.\n\nSegment 10.2.1.0/24 deep-dive\n- host_2_1_1_1 cannot reach any off-subnet IPs; ping to its default-gw 10.2.1.254 fails with “Destination Host Unreachable.”\n- However, it can reach 10.2.1.1:\n  - ping 10.2.1.1 succeeds (1–3 ms).\n  - arping 10.2.1.1 returns MAC 06:14:a5:9f:ff:3f.\n- router_dist_2_1 bridge-interface br0 is 10.2.1.1/24 (the actual L3 gateway for the segment).\n- router_dist_2_1 can ping host_2_1_1_1 successfully, confirming L2/L3 on the segment are fine.\n- DHCP configuration on dhcp_server for subnet 10.2.1.0/24 advertises “option routers 10.2.1.254” (misaligned with the real gateway 10.2.1.1):\n  - dhcpd.conf snippet: subnet 10.2.1.0 { … option routers 10.2.1.254; … }\n- Effect: host_2_1_1_1’s default route points to a nonexistent gateway, so ARP for 10.2.1.254 fails and all routed traffic (including DNS to 10.200.0.2) is blackholed. Local L2/L3 to 10.2.1.1 still works if explicitly addressed.\n\nLoad balancer and server reachability (control checks)\n- From host_1_1_1_1:\n  - curl http://web0.local and http://web99.local show normal name lookup (~4–12 ms), connect (~6–15 ms), and total times (~1.0–1.3 s).\n  - Ping to DNS, load balancer, and web servers all succeed.\n- This verifies DNS resolution, server farm reachability, and OSPF core are healthy overall.\n\nAnomalies detected\n- Incorrect default gateway assignment via DHCP in subnet 10.2.1.0/24.\n- Resulting client routing failure on host_2_1_1_1 (and likely any DHCP client in 10.2.1.0/24).\n\nFault localization\n- Primary faulty device: dhcp_server (dhcpd.conf for 10.2.1.0/24).\n- Impacted devices: DHCP clients in 10.2.1.0/24 (e.g., host_2_1_1_1).\n- Non-faulty components confirmed: router_dist_2_1 L3 SVI (10.2.1.1), access switching on that segment, OSPF adjacencies and routing across core and to server farm, DNS service, load balancer, and web servers.\n\nRoot cause\n- DHCP misconfiguration: option routers set to 10.2.1.254 on 10.2.1.0/24, which does not exist on that subnet. The actual gateway is 10.2.1.1 (router_dist_2_1 br0). This causes clients to install an invalid default route and lose connectivity to any off-subnet destination, including DNS and the server farm.\n\nEvidence (key excerpts)\n- host_2_1_1_1 routing: default via 10.2.1.254; ping 10.2.1.254 -> 100% loss; ping 10.2.1.1 -> success; arping 10.2.1.1 -> MAC reply.\n- router_dist_2_1: br0 10.2.1.1/24; can ping 10.2.1.12.\n- dhcp_server dhcpd.conf: subnet 10.2.1.0 { option routers 10.2.1.254; }.\n- OSPF neighbors: all Full; routing tables on distribution and server router consistent with design.\n- host_1_1_1_1 curl/http and ping tests: successful end-to-end to DNS and web services.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 51563, "output_tokens": 3844, "total_tokens": 55407, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 51200}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 2432}}}
